Rectangle inlet (incompressible, Umean driven)
==============================================

Demonstrates the syntheticTurbulenceInlet on a rectangular cross-section
with walls on all four sides and a constant area-averaged mean speed
(Umean = 10 m/s).

Geometry            Rectangle (single block).
Inlet target        Umean = 10 m/s.
Friction velocity   Auto-computed from the bulk Reynolds number.
Solver              foamRun, incompressibleFluid.

Run with:           ./Allrun
Clean with:         ./Allclean

Notes
-----
For a channel-style inlet (walls on two opposing sides, periodic on
the others) use the geometryMode "channel" instead. For the same
geometry driven by a target mass flow rate with a compressible
solver see rectangle_compress_mdot/.
